==English==

{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
Origin 1250-1300, from {{ME.}} ''[[daierie]]'' equivalent to ''[[daie]]'', ''[[deie]]'' ([[dairymaid]], from {{OE.}} ''[[dǣge]]'' ,[[bread maker]] or [[bread kneader]], see ''[[dheigh-]]'' in Indo-European roots), comparable with {{ON.}} ''[[deigja]]'' + ''[[Anglo-Norman]]'' ''[[-erie]]'' (place) (from {{OF.}}, see ''[[-ery]]'')

===Pronunciation===
* [[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'dæɻɪ/
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛəri|-ɛəri]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|dair|ies}}

# place, often on a [[farm]], where [[milk]] is processed and turned into products such as [[butter]] and [[cheese]]
# a shop selling dairy products
# (also ''dairy products'' or ''dairy produce'') products produced from [[milk]].
# {{NZ}} a [[corner-store]], [[superette]] or '[[mini-mart]]' of some description.

